Overview

Demonstrates Lead Operating System behavior when a lead fails validation requirements during processing.

The recording validates governance controls, failure handling, audit logging, and operational visibility when a record cannot proceed through the standard processing conveyor.

Recording Objectives

Demonstrate:

Lead creation

Lead intake processing

Lead enters Process OS

Validation failure occurs

Failure governance updates

Error logging

Audit logging

Final failed disposition
Recording Flow
Section 1

Lead Intake

Show:

Lead enters trigger sheet

Lead enters staging

Pipeline log update

Event logger update
Section 2

Lead Process

Show:

Lead enters PRC trigger

Sanitizer execution

Validation rule failure

Validation status update

Failure recorded
Section 3

Governance Layer

Show:

Validation Log update

Process Error Log update

Process Audit Log update
Section 4

Lead System

Show:

Error governance entry

Audit governance entry

State update

Final failed status
Success Criteria

Visible evidence of:

Lead_ID continuity

Correlation_ID continuity

Validation failure

Governance updates

Audit entries

Final failed state
